8. Simple Interest Engine

Formula

Interest = Principal \times Rate \times \frac{Days}{365}

⸻

Inputs

Principal
Annual Rate
Start Date
Calculation Date

⸻

Example

Principal = ₹100,000
Rate = 12%
Days = 180

Result:

Interest = ₹5,917.81

⸻

Rules

Actual Calendar Days

Used for calculation.

Rounding

2 Decimal Places

⸻

9. Katmiti Interest Engine

Purpose

Traditional Maharashtra Girvi method.

⸻

Core Principle

Partial payments:

Interest First
Principal Second

⸻

Katmiti Workflow

Month Start
      |
Interest Accrued
      |
Partial Payment
      |
Interest Settled
      |
Remaining Amount
      |
Principal Reduced
      |
New Base Principal
      |
Next Cycle Starts

⸻

Formula

Monthly Interest:

Monthly\ Interest = Principal \times Monthly\ Rate

⸻

Example

Month 1

Principal = ₹100,000
Rate = 2%

Interest:

₹2,000

⸻

Payment

₹5,000

Allocation:

₹2,000 Interest
₹3,000 Principal

⸻

New Principal

₹97,000

⸻

Next Cycle Base

₹97,000

⸻

Rules

Payment Order

Interest First
Principal Second

Mandatory.

⸻

Cycle

Configurable:

Monthly
Quarterly

